  "title": "Public Relations Officer - PRO (LTA Project, 5 days)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Oversee and strengthen the company’s market presence by implementing diverse marketing communication initiatives.</li><li>Plan and coordinate industry-related events to enhance brand recognition and engagement with key audiences.</li><li>Maintain and develop relationships with media outlets to ensure positive coverage.</li><li>Keep stakeholders informed about company activities through newsletters, campaigns, and other communication channels.</li><li>Act as the primary contact for customer feedback, collaborating with leadership to resolve concerns effectively.</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Diploma in Marketing, Communications, or equivalent.</li><li>At least 2 years of Public Relations experience within the construction industry, handling <strong>LTA projects.</strong></li><li>Skilled in client relations, with the ability to interact effectively with customers and key stakeholders.</li><li>Strong organizational skills, capable of managing multiple tasks and coordinating across various levels of the company.</li></ul><p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p><p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p><p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p><p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
